Arsenal skipper Pierre Emerick-Aubameyang returned to the starting eleven with a hat-trick that inspired the team to a 4-2 comprehensive defeat of Leeds United. He scored in the 13th, 41st and 47minutes while Bellerin got a goal in the 45th minute. Leeds responded with goals from Struijk and Hélder Costa but couldn’t do more to disturb a rampaging Arsenal side. Details shortly…